Chaos erupted at Glasgow Airport as a car burst into flames, crashing into the terminal in what British Prime Minister Gordon Brown deemed a deliberate attack.
Following the foiled car bomb plots in London, the security threat level was raised to "critical."
The incident in Glasgow was linked to the London attacks, indicating a coordinated effort.
Two suspects were arrested in connection with the events, emphasizing the imminent threat faced by Britain.
Security measures were heightened at airports across the country, urging the public to remain vigilant and support law enforcement efforts.
